<h4 id="3-2-2-on-input-a"><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/consistent-behavior-unpredictable-change.html">3.2.2 On Input (A)</a></h4>
<p>Changing the setting of any user interface component does not automatically cause a change of context unless the user has been advised of the behaviour before using the component.</p>
<h5 id="requirements-what-to-do">Requirements / What to do?</h5>

<ul>
<li>  Users can predict what a control such as a button or drop-down menu will do</li>
<li>  User interface components built with javascript have adequate and accurate ARIA labelling.</li>
</ul>
<h5 id="common-mistakes">Common mistakes</h5>

<ul>
<li>  Controls built with javascript lack appropriate ARIA information</li>
<li>  Form controls are used to trigger navigation without an explicit submit step, and without warning</li>
</ul>
